headline: Starbucks Could Take a Hit From 50% Brazilian Tariffs. The Cost of Coffee Beans Will Rise.
summary: The Trump administration threat of a 50% tariff on all Brazil imports will hit a variety of American companies.  Brazil is the largest coffee exporter to the U.S., accounting for 22% of the total in 2024.  The new tariffs could dent Starbucks earnings by 1.4%, wrote TD Cowen analyst Andrew Charles in a Thursday note.

headline: Starbucks China stake sale may fund turnaround, says Bernstein
summary: Investing.com -- A potential $10 billion sale of Starbucks’ China business could provide the company with financial firepower to accelerate its turnaround strategy, Bernstein analysts said.

headline: 3 Volatile Stocks Skating on Thin Ice
summary: Market swings can be tough to stomach, and volatile stocks often experience exaggerated moves in both directions. While many thrive during risk-on environments, many also struggle to maintain investor confidence when the ride gets bumpy.
